We're sad to report that Ed Asner passed away today.

Ed Asner was a decades long member of Democratic Socialists of America and a life long fighter for the heart and soul of the labor movement.

He will be missed.

Remember him by continuing to build the movements he built himself.

The struggle continues.

Video by @dsa_la

node.text:
Today we mourn the death of Senator Mike Gravel, who passed away this weekend. 

Senator Gravel gave us one of the best debate moments in history, and he truly believed service went beyond the Senate floor, where he is most known for reading the Pentagon Papers on the Senate floor.

In recent years he lent his name to run for President of the United States where volunteers formed what is now the @gravelinstitute, who we proudly support in our shared vision of taking down right wing disinformation with left wing facts and reality.

node.title: Rest in power, Senator Mike Gravel

Yesterday at Bernie Sanders' Biden/Harris rally Pennsylvania State House Rep @innamo nailed it:
.
"We cannot recover from historic traumas when new ones are inflicted on us every single day.
.
I'll be honest with y'all- electing Joe Biden will not cure what ails America. 
.
But it will stem the rising tide of authoritarianism and hate in our country.
.
This is about using our collective power to manifest the change that we demand to see in our society."
.

node.text:
We're sad to report that Ed Asner passed away today.

Ed Asner was a decades long member of Democratic Socialists of America and a life long fighter for the heart and soul of the labor movement.

He will be missed.

Remember him by continuing to build the movements he built himself.

The struggle continues.

Video by @dsa_la
